OL,3,CDisability organisation has been saved
OL,4,Cdays before closure
OL,6,FA Cumbrian disability organisation
OL,7,Fsaved days before closure by local
OL,8,Ffunders has been described as a
OL,9,F"lifeline" by service users.
OL,11,FThe Allerdale Disability Association
OL,12,Fannounced its closure due to a lack of
OL,13,Ffunding last month, after 48 years of
OL,14,Fsupporting people with impairments.
OL,16,FMichelle Corlett, says people were
OL,17,F"crying down the phone" as they were
OL,18,Ftold they could no longer use their
OL,19,Fservice.
