OL,3,CDisability organisation has been saved
OL,4,Cdays before closure
OL,6,FAnne Anderson, says it has been a
OL,7,F"lifeline" after losing her husband in
OL,8,F2017, she said: "I enjoy coming here
OL,9,Fbecause everybody's friendly. So you
OL,10,Fmake new, new friends by coming. I go
OL,11,Fout sometimes for dinner with some of
OL,12,Fthe group. But yeah, it means
OL,13,Feverything."
OL,15,FAnne Morgan, who's been using the
OL,16,Fservice for two years, said: "It was
OL,17,Ftremendous, it was. I mean, everybody
OL,18,Fclapped. Everybody was joyful. It's
OL,19,Fsomething you look forward to, you
OL,20,Fknow. They're all very, very nice."
